title: For Sale:  Winchester 1886 SRC 45 70 by Browning
postcontent:
This is a rare rifle. I'm askin $1350 obo. The 1886 is considered one of the best actions every designed and this Browning is considered one of the strongest and due to modern medal advances. The fit and finish of this rifle is superb. Being that the 1886 was a John Browning design, Browning made a small number of full length rifles and SRCs to commemorate the history. The rifles were made in 1986 and the SRC in 1991. They are made true to the original design with no tang safety or rebounding hammer (that causes light primer strikes) as the newer Winchester have. 

This rifle is in next to new condition with about 30 rounds through it. It was purchased from Turnbull years ago and never used. It is chambered in 45 70. They are only going up in price every year.
